Definitions:

<home-dir>
	The RNS path to the directory where the user should "login". A script in the format .glogin.xml or .glogin.js should exist there.

Description:
	This tool allows a user to "login" to a particular directory, and then executes the .glogin.xml or .glogin.js script here. If both .glogin.xml and .glogin.js exist, then both scripts are executed.

Code:

Implementing Class 
    edu.virginia.vcgr.genii.client.cmd.tools.ShellLoginTool
